postcontent:
Selling my nearly new Sig P238 SAS model. Comes with all the case candy, one 6 round magazine – all the stuff that came with it new. Note this is the SAS model, with stainless slide and rounded corners. It was made for pocket carry.

Great pistol. Nice trigger, small, compact, light. Very accurate. Extremely reliable. No issues whatsoever in the 500 or so rounds I put through it.

Bright Night Sights.

I’ve owned an LCP, Colt Mustang, Kahr P380, Taurus TCP738. This is by far a better pistol than all of those. The LCP has a terrible trigger, the Mustang was a feeding nightmare, the Kahr has a recoil spring that makes slide retraction a real challenge for some, and the TCP is light but has a very long pull and tiny grip. Overall the Sig is a far better gun.

So why am I selling it? I’m lefthanded, and finally decided to get another Sig P238 SAS identical to this but with the ambi safety.  So this one, with the standard safety for a righthander is no longer needed.

Price is firm. I will not respond to lower offers if and until the market dictates. I can just keep it rather than discount it too much.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom AR-15, 5.56 x 45
postcontent:
Don't be fooled by people building ARs in their basements.  Every AR someone builds will be "custom" because they piece it together from parts they buy.

If you buy an AR, find out what type of warranty comes with it and how they can honor it or you may be in for a surprise if it doesn't work, jams, things break, etc.

Like on other sites, there should be some sort of "reputation/trustworthy" rating, but there is none, so beware of who you are purchasing from and what you are purchasing.

title: For Sale:  Custom Stainless Glock 21 Gen 3 with 25 round mag
postcontent:
Glock 21 Gen 3 45 ACP.    Price is 525.00 Firm.  No trades on this one.  Pictures dont do it justice.

This Glock 21 comes with 2 factory 13 round mags and 1 Kriss Vector 25 round mag (80 dollar mag).  It also comes with a Glock soft case.  This gun also has a Ghost trigger and an extended slide release installed.

This gun was sent off to Cummings Custom Refinishing for their CPII coating.  This is a plating process, not a cheap spray on coating.  Both the slide and barrel was plated with their CPII coating.  You can read more about it below.  This coating also has a lifetime warranty.  Very easy to clean up after shooting.  And this coating self lubricates itself.

CPII is a true composite plating process. It is an Electroless Nickel / Boron Nitride tank based plating system that incorporates Boron Nitride particles within the matrix of a phosphate system. Benefits include exceptionally low coefficient of friction, superior release and excellent wear resistance. CP II is perfect for applications that require the lubrication of Teflon but need more wear resistance. As wear occurs fresh particles of Boron Nitride are exposed continuing to ensure the lubricating factors though out. CPII also allows longer firing periods between cleaning and makes cleaning of your gun a breeze CPII is a multi facetted plating process that offers outstanding rust and corrosion protection Up to 10 times the protection of other plating such as Nickel/Teflon and Chrome CPII is far from your standard plating it is a true composite plating process that is made possible by the breakthroughs in Nano Technology CPII is also an Eco friendly process. CPII is the color similar to a Bead Blasted Stainless.                   http://www.ccrrefinishing.com/information.html

I believe the ser # puts it somewhere in the 70's so it's when Winchester was still making great guns and actually owned it. It's not a pre 64 but still a great timeless classic that will live in infamy. I also have a scope that's noting special but will get the job done if you don't prefer iron sights. It's got the quick detach mount already installed if you wish to go that route. I personally just love to let that gun run with open sights and do what John M. Browning intended it to do. Anyhow that's my speech let me know if you need more pics or info. Great gun, runs all day, ammo is everywhere, shoot straight, drink water, and change your socks. 

Semper Fi

title: For Sale:  1970s Browning  Auto "light twelve" 12 gauge  shotgun
postcontent:
1970s browning auto light twelve, 12 gauge shot gun. 2 original barrels. 

Was my grandfathers gun. It's Belgium made and from what I remember he bought this in Europe when he was stationed there. The shotgun was used for skeet shooting. For 30 years the shotgun was in my grandfathers storage in a bag. I have had the last few years and have shot it several times. Works perfect and still super accurate.  One barrel is 20 inches and the other is 18. (I believe from researching it) one is chocked. Wood Is in a amazing condition for 40 years old. Few rust spots on the outside, internals have no rust. 

Super rare to have this shotgun with both barrels.

title: For Sale/Trade:  RUGER "FLAT GATE" 3-SCREW SINGLE-SIX 22 FLAT TOP REVOLVER 1955 MFG
postcontent: This is a rare, early, unconverted, and original Ruger 3-screw old model Single-Six. Has the desirable "flat gate" loading gate only seen on very early guns. This 1955 gun was made in the third year of production (there were only 51 made in the first two years!). Ruger offered to convert all their old model revolvers to include the "transfer bar safety kit". This gun comes with the new conversion kit parts still in bags that have never been installed in the gun - it is unconverted . Includes box and paperwork. Mechanically excellent. Very tight and very accurate. Finish shows scattered oxidization overall. Firearm trades or cash offers.

The ND3 is a green laser, not a cheap LED. You adjust it to fill up the view of your scope, and it's like having perfect night vision. Being a laser, it projects about 500 yards as a "wide beam" and "miles" as you narrow the beam. Also, the laser makes any animal's eyes reflect in a way that a light will not do. 

I used this unit to hunt wild boar in North Carolina last Spring, and it was awesome! This is NOT just the ND3 itself, but rather the kit that contains all of the accessories. It's got all of the mounting hardware for any riffle including AR's. It also comes with the pressure switch that can be stuck to the side of your riffle, which I have NOT used.
